{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_18","type":"agent_message","text":"The native test does fail, but not with `Missing*RegistrationError`; it’s a behavior regression in the native executable: boot delegation misses `javax.crypto.Cipher`, `ContextFinder#getResources()` drops a parent resource, and `LoggerAdmin` never registers. That usually means reachability metadata is incomplete even when the runtime doesn’t throw explicit missing-registration exceptions, so I’m inspecting the tests plus any traced/native-image config to identify the concrete resource/reflection gaps."}}
