{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_86","type":"agent_message","text":"The runtime tracing flags are the part this GraalVM doesn’t support, but the repo also bakes `--exact-reachability-metadata` into the `nativeTraceImage` binary itself. I’m building that exact-metadata binary and running it directly, without `-XX:TraceMetadata*`, to see if the remaining failures turn into actionable `Missing*RegistrationError` output."}}
