{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_126","type":"agent_message","text":"The debug output gives two important facts. `ParentContextClassLoader#getResources()` already works in native, so the `ContextFinder` failure is specifically in the library’s `ClassLoader.getResources` fallback path, not in the resource itself. Separately, `framework.start()` leaves the service registry completely empty, so I’m adding one more temporary hook to print framework error events during startup; that should tell us whether startup is aborting on a specific missing class/resource or whether this is a runtime bug outside metadata."}}
